NIGHTSABER (GB) coaxed from the gate, raced forwardly placed along the inside before advancing to take command just inside six furlongs to go, showed the way under pressure and yielded near the seven-sixteenths, spun two to three wide for home and faltered.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: J D ADVANTAGE sat riderless behind the gate as they attempted to load a stubborn rival then was reluctant to load herself, moved in while showing good speed, vied between foes passing the nine-sixteenths then inside of a foe, dropped from the two path to the rail early on the turn, dueled gamely with the runner-up from that point to the wire and narrowly prevailed under strong urging. LAOCHI bumped with a rival at the start, was taken in hand briefly early the moved up to get a short lead at the nine-sixteenths, vied outside from that juncture, dropped from the three path to the two path early on the turn, dueled with the winner from that point to the finish and just missed in a game effort. JUST A NYQUIST was urged along off the pace, went four then three wide around the turn, pursued the top two in the stretch, gained on those foes late and finished willingly for the show. SPOOKY LADY bumped with an opponent at the start, showed good speed on the inside of foes, dropped back near the half-mile pole, chased inside around the turn and tired. MISCHIEF MOTION moved out under urging early, saved ground around the turn and failed to threaten. VIRTUAL BEAUTY raced well back in the field, dropped from the four path to the two path early on the turn and was no factor. Non-winners of a race other than maiden, claiming or starter allowed 2 lbs. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. Closed Saturday, January 7, 2023 with 12 Nominations.
